                    <TextBlock TextAlignment="Center" FontSize="48" Foreground="white" Canvas.Left="12" Canvas.Top="10">
                                Keys and Scales
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock  FontSize="30" Foreground="White" Canvas.Left="12" Canvas.Top="117">
                        Most music is in a particular key. If we say that a song is "in the key of C," this means that the pitch C
                        <LineBreak/>
                        sounds like the most stable “home note” (or tonic) for the song.
                        <LineBreak/>
                        Likewise, most songs use notes within a particular scale — a collection of notes in order from low to high.
                        <LineBreak/>
                        <LineBreak/>
                        Here is the C Major Scale:
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock TextAlignment="Center" FontSize="48" Foreground="white" Canvas.Left="12" Canvas.Top="322">
                                C->D->E->F->G->A->B->C
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock  FontSize="30" Foreground="White" Canvas.Left="12" Canvas.Top="391">
                        Major scales are often described as sounding 'happy' or 'bright', but can be used for very diferent purposes
                        <LineBreak/>
                        <LineBreak/>
                        Here is the C minor Scale:
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock TextAlignment="Center" FontSize="48" Foreground="white" Canvas.Left="12" Canvas.Top="516">
                                C->D->Eb->F->G->Ab->Bb->C
                    </TextBlock>
                    <TextBlock  FontSize="30" Foreground="White" Canvas.Left="12" Canvas.Top="585">
                        Minor scales are darker than a Major scale, and are associated with sadness.
                        <LineBreak/>
                        But this association with happiness and sadness can be misleading, and should not be treated as a given.
                        <LineBreak/>
                        For instance: Just Dance (Lady Gaga) is in a minor key, and No Surprises (Radiohead) is in a Major key.
                    </TextBlock>
                </Canvas>
